	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>evildragon</b> [ Fri Dec 14, 2007 12:32 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">peppers wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">if the onley problem with the old light guns is the video signel the console outputs why dose the Wii use something so inaccurate for there pointer controlls</div>
<br />Well it's not the signal.
<br />
<br />It's the image processing that TV's introduce.  My HDTV by itself, introduces a delay that is approximately 1-2 frames behind, this makes the zapper not function and miss a shot.
<br />
<br />The professional scaler I used however only introduces a 4ms delay, and works perfectly fine, as long as the scaler is set to a native mode of the HDTV.
<br />
<br />LCD's still failed the test, possibly from native latency.  Didn't test a plasma.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


